This paper deals with natural language understanding, specifically with the composition of meaning from individual words to sentences and then to discourse. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of statistical and logical resources, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions question answering and anaphora resolution, which are topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic web (cs.SI).
